OpenShift master includes a built-in OAuth server for authenticating and authorising users into clusters
for all-in-one mode of setup, the default of OAuth config value is AllowAllIdentityProvider in /etc/origin/master/master-config.yanl, it allows all users logging in without verifying passwords,
if a user doesnt exist, it auto-creates it. 
the value can be set to DenyAllIdentityProvider which would stop all users logging in, in this case, admin has to manually creates ans enables new users.
